column5: Activity Description

column3: Ladder Workout. First half @ LT, second half @RE/lower
column5:
Ladder workout - 1 (1) 2 (2) 3 (3) 4 (3) 5 (3) 4 (3) 3 (2) 2 (1) 1
First half at LT @ ~5:35-5:40 pace then progression to RE half through 5. RE @5:25 for 5 & 4. then 5:18 for 3, 5:12 for 2, 4:54 for 1 (paces). Very good workout and happy with my performance especially at the RE and lower stages and the 5 and 4 minute lengths.
2xCourse hills. I walked in between and it be like that so the pace is slow. Got peer-pressured into jogging a mile back but it felt good so it was worth it.
Spicy 200's. Used my mid-d spikes and I just felt really fast which is nice. 30/31 on each one so I was pleased
On, steady, on, steady, on 4min break 3 times. 3x400M w/1:40 rest. 71-73 on every on rep.

column3: Iceberg. Oh shit the Titanic has its eyes closed. And it just sunk like me during this run

column5: 💩💩💩 <--- This race.
2 miles to see if I need to sit today's workout. Coach thinks I should still do it and I don't think I should. I'm not getting any push from a right leg cause of my ankle.
Mile splits were way too slow. This wasn't even a workout to me cause it was just so shit. Coach is finally giving me 2 days off thank jesus

column3: Turn it upside down and it's a t-rex with a long tail

column5: Feeling a little better. This is such a weird injury and the trainers haven't been any use so idk what to do really. I upped my cadence to ~180 and my ankle was feeling better so idk how to fix this long-term but this may be a short-term option

Some more cross training since I didn't really run today. Decided to switch it up a little and hit the pool since it's been a while since I have swam. And I realized how tough swimming can be. Decided to 12 minutes of constant swim. Then 5x25M to round it off. Tracking swim laps is harder than track laps so the distance isn't correct but oh well.
Some biking after swimming to just flush muscles out and what not. My leg is feeling a lot better so I'm happy with everything. I'll see about running tomorrow, as long as my form is ok
My watch got fucked up I guess?? Did an inner loop with Miami. My leg was feeling better and I wasn't limping as much so that's good. Still hurts like a bitch.

Post-run biking. I'm officially out for the next week but I'm doing 8 hours worth of biking and swimming in GAC this next week so exciting. I'll have some time to watch some Netflix and finish a show. This sucks since this will be the first meet that I won't be running. Hopefully I'm going to get better soon

column3: Rip me. Hopefully not Rip the season?

column5: First 20 miler bike. Just cruised and did a guided blind freshman route. Sad to not be running but this will help me recover. I thought hills sucked while running, hills suck even more while biking. Quads hurty from hills
Jk it's not that bad. Decided to hop in the pool for my morning double today. Did 2x5x100M with a 50M super chill backstroke in between. Swimming is wack and now my arms are gonna probably hurt.

Took canal path hella far today and it was a good time. Definitely slowed down a little on the back end but I'm still getting used to biking more extended distances. Listened to my rock playlist that's a bop. (Hi Todd S, I hope you had a good bike ride :)

column3: Ladle cause I be eating this shit up
column5: This was more of a chill ride. Didn't want to go too hard or too easy. Almost got hit by a car only 3 miles in which was wack. I don't think Eddie would have been happy if I got hit.
8:15 2 mile warmup. 8:03 2 mile cooldown. Both were on the spin cycle.

Decided to do a fartlek on the cycle machine after cheering on all the dudes at the genny meet today. But it was 6x1.5mile with a minute active ride rest. Was really consistent in my splits as I keep lower them as the workout went along. 4:44, 4:32, 4:33, 4:27, 4:29, 4:15 splits for the 1.5 miles. Honestly the first two were the hardest then I got into a groove and just cranked them the fuck out. Happy with today and I'm scheduled to come back to run on Monday :)

Long chill bike that felt pretty good. Decided to kick it down a notch in terms of speed for today and focus more on being consistent over the long distance. I'm back running tomorrow and I can't be happier

column3: O for oh man Im back
column5: Finally back to sorta running. Was on the track with Nick for a 15 minute session. Did 400M running, 200M walking. Had pain and my form was off for a while but I'm trying to fix my form rhythm. Still gradually building with a goal in mind.
Post-"run" cross training. Chill whatever
Some swimming. Did 26 minutes of aqua jogging then 11 of regular swimming with the leg buoy cause of my injury. Aqua jogging was lowkey hard af and a good workout.
Swim ladder workout. 200M warmup 100,150,200,200,150,100. @2:00/100yd pace w/ 1:00 rest in between. Then 200M cooldown. Only upper body since lower leg injury.

Trainers said if it's painless it's fine so I tested out biking today and it was gucci. Didn't feel any pain. This was my first set of biking and way more intense as I did 10min wu @200watt then minute @300 minute @200 x5.
Chill cooldown bike with Jared. Had some good conversations about track and the upcoming which is getting me pumped up to start running again
Tried to bike this morning. Felt good until 15 minute then I felt a little pain in my leg and immediately shut it down. Not taking any risks right now

Workout in the gac yet again :( This was better than usual workouts. Did the on's at 275-300 watts. Quads were empty and heavy at the same time so yike. However, this was a good mental workout as I kept pushing myself and look past the pain. Maybe that's what these bike workouts will help with. Trying to look on the bright side and eventually get back to running soon
Night swim w/Kyra and Ethan. I got cooked by Kyra. Also my triceps were on fire cause of lifting
Used a road bike instead of the hybrid and shit was flying. I didn't feel bad at all and this was a really good chill effort. Andres and I had some good convos and had a really good time 11/10
Is GAC spelled b-o-r-i-n-g?
Hm 16.9 MPH that's pretty nice
L since I took one on the return part of this ride. 25 MPH winds didn't make it any easier and now my quads feel fried.

column3: T-1 week until I can run
column5: Jesus is King was on repeat for the entire time and I was absolutely jamming. It was fire. 9/10 after having listening to it some more.
Closer and closer
Longer session today but I felt good. Get my heart rate up high for an extended period of time is feeling really good
Back at it again. Feeling really good lately. Super excited and feeling overall a lot happier. Release those good ass endorphins
Close. Also more chilled out training. No big comments just daily stuff
Slow asl today cause my quads have been on fire today. I am more sore right now than I was the entire summer training/preseason.
Post-lift work. Excitement and everything else is building to start running again. Yeeeeeee
Got  put on limited status by the doctor today and got to run walk. Did a mile of 200 run, 200 walk just as precaution. Felt really good and getting back to form.
Have to do this in between days cause "re-injury chances are highest the two weeks when coming back"
Another whatever session of cross training to recover for running tomorrow.

column3: First Snow Run of the Season
column5: Two laps in the snow just started to welcome itself which took me for a hot loop. It wasn't that bad but it was still like oh shit snow. Also, felt really good. Comeback szn
Getting real sick of the motivation signs in the GAC.
There's a lot of spicy rain outside today so I was indoor
Last time I ran outside it was 80 and sunny what the hell happened. Wore my lucky race socks to give the regionals squad some good luck. You all are gonna crush it
Am I finally a distance runner again?
Big Boy Miles. I've been really good lately and I'm hyped to get back into fast running. Also, GO WEN great race I hope I did my part to make you guys run fast.
Last Rochester run for the week. Get ready for some ~nice~ Chicago runs
Ah my beautiful out and back city runs. L since 35MPH winds decide to welcome me back.

I probably sorta totally went a little too fast. But I was feeling really good and I think that it's time to start doing workouts again. I also want to run more. Only 5 days a week feels weird. And only doing 5 miles. Wack
On the indoor track since me no like snow

Snow
Lmao this was supposed to be a recovery and this was no recovery pace
Was supposed to be 6 miles but Kortsy took a wrong turn sooo. Also shoutout to Andres for being my number one fan, I love you

Recovery run since I didn't one last week. A little slow for my liking however I was running with Jacen and didn't want to take it too fast. It started to hail midway through the run and my skin started to hurt since I was wearing shorts. It be like that. Also sausage fest is tomorrow and idk how mentally and physically prepared. I hope that the entire house doesn't break cause let's be real it could totally happen
Today is the day. When boys become men.
Wanted to zoom so I zoomed. This was actually a pretty solid run. I definitely felt it in mile 4 but on the last mile I just started to fly.

No, I don't. I hate snow. Especially this type of snow. This snow just stuck to my chest and was like wet and cold. But actually this run flew by with Kortsy and Leo. We just had some fun and had some good convos.

Pre-finals anxiety run. Fun run to do to just clear my mind of shit. Was absolutely destroyed by the head wind for the first 4 miles then it turned to tail wind and I started to pick up the pace. None of the run felt hard expect that last half-mile where my pace was LT pace. Good solo tho
My body hurts

13 degrees with -1 wind chill as I left to do the warmup. This was a huge mental challenge with the cold and being sick and my first workout back from injury. However, I felt like I was doing well for the first half and then for some reason I wasn't able to lower my pace anymore. My legs weren't really fatigued I just couldn't go faster. It was wack but pacing was actually faster than I expected. Going out in 5K pace was not it. I really need to relearn how to pace workouts.

I'm back. I had a nasty sinus infection for the past few days so I decided to take two days off. But now I'm doing hella better. Heart rate was high mainly cause I was completely unable to breath through my nose. I planned on more backloading my runs this week and welp I fucked myself over so imma be a tad under 45 this week

50 and sunny so it was beautiful. Wanted to go a little faster since I took two workouts off cause I was sick. Haha someone should run with me ... haha jk .... unless?
Catcall tally: "You're gay" - II "Nice legs" - I "Looks like it's summer" - III so that's how this run went.
Calm recovery run around the neighborhood. Got a love tap from a car today but we're doing all good

This workout was sponsored and fueled by Deep Dish Pizza. The lunch and preworkout of champions. So, this workout was interesting cause I started trash talking it after the first 2 and during the middle then the lactic acid hit my legs like a truck. I'm still a little out of shape, in terms of doing those longer workouts so these are rough but we're just vibing
Eddie Claus gave me a steady easy run for today. But I felt good and just went on feel. The backend slowed a little but oh well
3 miles to start then .6 of accelerations then finished with 4.9 miles. Boring run tbh, nothing cool happened and there wasn't anyone interesting to look at. Oh well
Last run in Chicago before I go to France (said with a french accent). This run was just eh. All houses
Short run after a long day of traveling. I was supposed to do a long run but I wasn't able to cause of time so I'm going to add some miles tomorrow morning before the workout.

Had to make up miles from yesterday so I went out to do this. Probably one of the most beautiful runs that I have ever done. Was able to go through the city and along the river which was sick. Got lost at one point, it be like that but it was still worth it
Can Italian people put their dogs on leashes?????

(4:41-6:47) (4:42-7:08) (4:46-7:16) (4:41-6:58) (4:56-7:30) (4:42-7:47) (4:59-7:22) (4:57-7:37) 
First, I know that my schedule is going off the fucking rails. I'm trying my best while being away from home and doing stuff in Europe. Second, this workout got me good. It was a lot harder than I thought it would be. I was hard struggling on the second one, for a sense of it. However, I kept the paces under 5 the entire time and had a good amount of 4:40's. The arena that I did it around had a bunch of people so sometimes I had to navigate through them and move onto the grass and back to cement and what not.

Cool down from the workout. Went around the park and the castle that was near as I was doing it blind. It was actually really cool. Gave me Grant Park or Central Park vibes as I was able to just run anywhere.

I got fucking lost in Venice. So I started this run without phone cause I thought I knew where I was going since I was just going to follow the river to the other side of island. Well that was a fucking lie. I turned too soon and crossed the river and it was all over. Then I stopped my watch at 4 so I could ask for directions. Where I stopped on the map is when I should have gone north but homie told me that I was west and in a different part of the island so I went east and then ended up on the other side of island and I was like well what the fuck mate?? But then I got back. So this run was probably more like ~6 miles

column3: Very very very early candidate for Run of the Year (Innsbruck 2020)
column5: Holy moly this run was absolutely beautiful but hella tough. Went mountain running and got destroyed by the hills. However once I got to the 4 miler it was beautiful. Had to turn back early and not do my planned loop since the roads were pure ice and it was getting dark.

column3: Stairs in place of a recovery run
column5: Had to do a stair workout in place of a run today since I didn't have time to run without going when it was dark. Did 6x (1 Step up- 1 Step down) (2 Step up - 1 Step down) (3 step up - 1 step down) @4 flights of stairs. Not hard, just needed to do something today. Also added 30 minutes of core/other body weight work
Back at my dad's military base for the morning. Time to get this bread

Moving workouts around still. Did this on the track at my dad's military base and it felt so good to be on a track for a workout. Was cruising for the most part but I couldn't get much faster on the mile intervals. Didn't hit 4:40's like I wanted to but I was around 5:05-5:10 for the others so I am satisfied with this for now. Need to just gain back some more fitness but I am finally getting back my workout groove
(5:11-7:10) (4:45-7:22) (5:03-7:19) (4:51-7:17) (5:12-7:24) (5:01-7:10) +Day 2 lift
Did 2 miles to start then did the workout along a pathway by La Seine. Wasn't too hard but I was able to flex on all those Parisians.

Elevation gain was 420, nice. Another Paris run. Did the first two miles with my dad then headed out to get the remaining miles. There was a roadblock at one point that made me go back about a quarter of a mile. Flying for the most part

This was a mediocre run at best. There were quite a bit of hills that I wasn't expecting but I didn't have a route planned at all so I was running wherever felt good. Forced myself on that last mile but I'm glad that I did it

6 miles + 10x(8s hill sprints). Again in hilly luxembourg. This time I actually knew where I wanted but that still didn't stop me from messing up the route. Felt miles better than yesterday which is good. Maybe I'm becoming a hill runner.... lmao no
Went to the castle that's near my dad's apartment. Was sick to see and it was a short and nice shakeout before my workout. Very slow

2 miles to workout then 5 minute cool down. This was probably the best and easiest workout that I have done since injury. Also, the progression wasn't exactly there but times were negatives so I'll take it. I did this today since I'll be traveling for 16 hours tomorrow.

I forgot snow is a thing and Rochester gets a lot of snow.

Rainy warmup
Rain, rain, rain
Long run with the boys. Split off with Leo, Ivan and Blaine and we went way too far, to me at least

Amazing workout to start off the year. This felt a lot easier than I expected as I felt like I could talk during the 600's. Also had a steady progression for the reps which was good to see. Distance is probably wrong since I walked in between reps
1:50.5; 1:46.6; 1:46.1; 1:45.5, 1:44.4
Recovery Cobbs with Leo and Blaine. Good run to flush out the muscles, get some miles in, and prepare for tomorrow's workout
Got through the first two sets then coach told Blaine and I to max out the 7th then we capped the workout there. Lungs and breathing felt really good and not bad but legs were gone cause of lift
Can someone give a lowly mid-d runner some miles?
Comeback Szn

First race back from injury in a bit of time. Was using this race as a big rust buster and seeing where I'm at in terms of speed and endurance. I'll say that I did fairly well. Kept to my race strats of keeping it back for the first 800 then start going the last 800. I only made a mistake or two but they were small and things to acknowledge and fix going to the next race next weekend. Before the race I was getting really anxious and scared for a variety of reasons but once that gun shot, it mainly went away. As well, pissed scotty came out on the last two laps. Coach told me that I should have gone a little sooner and get up in the pack sooner but again I was feeling scared cause of the competition.

55.5 for 400M. I felt a large mix of anxiety and looseness. I negative split by .2s so I probably could have gone a lot faster but I was leading and I didn't have anything to catch. Good race to finish up the RIT meet
Snowy, icy, slippery run with Leo and Blaine.
Chilly cool down. Temps were in the low teens which is tuff

73 70 68 66 64 64 was intended.
74 70 66 65 63 64 was results. 
This was a mediocre workout. I was very hungry and tired during it cause I ate early(and probably not enough) and went to bed late. Hit the paces that mattered the most which was good but I'm still not super satisfied as I got a little frustrated which I got to keep in check. On to the Wednesday and looking to Saturday

Decided to just run various campus loops since I didn't want to deal with snow this morning. Saw Ollie and Helena walking to college town which was neato. A lot warmer than expected as I brought out a warmer top and I definitely didn't need it.
Run with my boy Alec. It was such a chill run and a really nice to breathe and just remember why I run
Absolute jank warmup since I didn't want to run in the snow and Trawick was like "wa don't be a baby"

30, 29.5, 29.5 -> Intended
Hit 30 for each of the first set. Hit 29.5 for each expect for a random 30 on #2. Then was 29.5 or below for each on the last set. Absolutely vibing with Blaine for this workout. Tough but manageable which was really good to do. Good confidence booster going into Saturday
Cool down with Blaine. Talked about time control which is always a decent topic

Mile race at Naz. 5 second PR from last week, scored 3 points, and qualified for conference so pretty good January race. Took the first 200 in a 31 which was a "mistake" but more and more I'm taking it not as a mistake since my splits were constant 33's after that lap. If anything the kick wasn't what I was looking for but it doesn't matter as it is back to training and get some other races in.
Warmed up for the 4x400 since I was an alternate and Mark was a question mark up until the first heat to run. Did a light mile and 2 strides but Mark ended up running so I didn't have to

Long run with Kenjamin. Did a 8 mile park ave (??? idk if that's the name) then 3 solo miles. One of my favorite routes cause it's long and I get a city vibe from it which reminds me of running at home a little

2:30, 2:26, 2:22, 2:20 was paces and I hit each one on the dot so that was a really good feeling. I started to get shin splits during the workouts which makes me nervous since the stress fracture was in my tibia so I'm going to be extra proactive and what not. Hopefully, training doesn't get impacted
cold

Mid-d workouts give no miles so these long recovery runs feel weird. Also at like mile 6 I got the same shin pain as before and that's really worrisome. May have to scrap the workout but we'll see how the warmup goes

Oh fuck it's back. Shin pain is not doing too well. Was supposed to have a workout today but I scraped it and I'm taking tomorrow off too. Also, I got pulled from the Cornell meet which really sucks since I wanted to get a competitive 800 in. Putting everything in recovery. Idk why this is happening, only guess is that I'm in spikes for too long and that's killing my lower legs
And I be back. Felt ok for the first run back. Not much else that's big
Started a bailey's with the fellas but only did an out and back since I was only doing a little. Legs felt really really good which is good news
Can't wait for it to be colder at every track meet

3:06, 2:25, 1:43, 1:04, (46.4, 46.6, 46.0, 47.2, 45.5).
Really good workout as it's my first 1500-5k one. Did it with Ivan which really pushed me on the longer reps then pushed him on the 300's. Maybe, this cements me moving up to 1500-5k training. I'm sorry my fellow mid-d dudes.

Recovery day since my body just hurts right now. It is so hard to get to bed before 11 on morning lift days which doesn't allow me to recover fully, but 7h + 30min nap was good. ALSO, can UHS stop having me reschedule appointments, it have had to do so 3 times for just a physician appointment.
Did a steady run in the cemetery with Alec. Straight zooming and then dovetailed the last mile. Felt really good and really fun to get a steady run finally

ZOOM ZOOM Wow this came out of left field. Felt good before the race but not that good. We went out in 56-high since there were rabbits which just pushed me since I was third at 400 and then just cranked out the 400 in a 60-mid. Really happy with this race. Thought I could escape the 800 training group but I have no clue what I'll be racing for the next meets. All that matters is that I ran to run another week for regionals

Zoom zoom pt.2. My legs were still lactic from the 800 so this was interesting. I also was racing to catch people and I ended up getting a Naz relay which felt good. This 53 and that 1:57 800 is really hurting my 1500-5k training group chances
s n o w
Failed cobs into a park ave with Nate Lawson

Very enjoyable run in the city. A ton of fun even though it was solo since I was the only 1500-5k BU guy at 3:30. Good quick run before tomorrow's workout and then preparing for BU. City runs are great when you're not running with others cause I can be as reckless as I want.

51, 3:15, 31 paces. 51.5, 50.5, 3:14, 3:11, 3:12, 31.2, 31.4, 29.6. Ended up going faster on every rep except the 200's. This was a good tune up workout for Boston and got some more 1k work which felt good. Overall, this workout felt very comfortable and that I wasn't pushing it hard so that's good.
Running with Blaine and Collin is like running with two children

First two miles were accidentally stress miles since I was definitely feeling the pressure of the meet from just being there. Went out and saw a friend tho which was nice even just talking for a few minutes. Nervous but hopefully prepared for tomorrow

Scotty is the name, overthinking and choking at important meets is the game. More seriously, I thought about this meet way too much which just fucked me up. This meet was on my mind all week and I just had some really high expectations for it. Legs went lactic at 600 when it's usually past the 1000 so that was a problem. Probably cause I opened too fast. Needed this type of race to humble me in a sense but it's time to get some really good training, get faster, get confidence back, and run fast.
Stress/disappointment cool down miles
Long run with the boys. Watch broke so the heart rate is way over what it actually was since it was a solid 3 inches from my wrist. Shoutout to Danielle for fixing it with a hair tie, that was huge

Ouchie, I got cooked like a turkey on thanksgiving day. First speed work in 2+ weeks and oh boy was it a shock to the system. Hit paces for every rep, until the 400 which was supposed to be 90% and then I dropped a 59 so you know, it be like that sometimes. But I m still satisfied with how it went so that's good.
V slow today since my legs are still recovering from the lactic acid workout yesterday. Forgot to ice bathe today so my legs are gonna be hurting during this 3k

Not too bad for my first track race above a mile and being a mid-d runner. Decided to try out the 3k to see the range and maybe qualify for conference. Was doing really good the first 2400 and was on 35, 36 pace but then my legs were just like "uh dudeski what are you doing, we were supposed to stop 800 ago". Hit 38, 39 for the last laps. So I feel fine about it and maybe with some more long distance I could put work in but I think I wanna stick with the mile. Also, ran with the boys and it was really fun and definitely made this race a lot easier

Been feeling really overwhelmed lately so this solo run was really needed. Wanted to clear my head and was able to do so. Wanted to do a buffalo road but the canal trail was snowed out so then I decided to just run around without really thinking. Wasn't really looking at my watch for this run and just went on feel. Which felt really good and relaxed the entire time.
Ankur loop with Ryley, Leo, Nate and Ken. Had a lot of fun and the time just passed by. I'm really excited for the next weeks and to finally run a championship race

3:20, 2:34, 58, 43, 28, 13.5 -> 3:17, 2:34, 58, 41.3, 27.1, 12.9.
Fun workout day the week of championships. Didn't feel too hard really which makes me feel pretty confident. Did this solo but it didn't change my attitude. Also, dropped a 15 first 100 on the 400 which was like ope guess I gotta do a 43 now so yeah the speed transition got to me
Collin and I didn't decide on a route so this shit show of a route happened.
My fav route (most of the time).
A chilly one today. Coach had us OYO for today since winds are 30+ which is wild. Leo almost got hit by a bus on Elmwood so the run felt like I was just at home.

Idk why I have been shitting the bed in the mile+ lately. It's like I have been going lactic way too quickly and just can't do anything about it. But this race was different since it was the DMR and it was the championship. Got the lead and went 66 which was perfect, but then after that I was clueless. I had no clue what my 800 split was cause coach didn't say it or I didn't hear him. I had no clue where the other runners were cause I didn't hear them either. And it was some general confusion and I didn't race well. It wasn't a bad race but a stupid one. I should be able to kick out the last 100M but like I have no clue. My hamstring have been getting beaten to shreds during these mile races. Hopefully once we get ready for outdoor that I can get a 1500 training cycle going and I can feel better

Wow that race was interesting and dirty. But also not the smartest race I have run. We got out good and hit the pace for 400 (56-57) but then this RPI guy decided to be a fucking asshole and race like a little bitch. On the turn, he decided to shove me and elbow me as he was passing on the inside and even went out of the lane. I got tripped up and lost so much momentum going into the next laps as I saw Blaine move up. And then I got passed up by Ithaca and Leo and was just like fuck, are you kidding me. But then I was able to somehow to kick the last 100 and pass to get up to 4 in the heat. And that RPI guy ended up getting DQ'ed and good cause he raced dirty and he didn't have a good time so he can go fuck off. 
I also don't want to pin this time on him because overall I still did well and got 5th and I'm happy but I know that 1:56 is very possible next weekend. I just have to get that second half under 60 and then it'll happen.
This route, led by Collin, was a rebranded high falls. Only 1 mile was unique and this is a direct call out @Collin.
GVP adventure loop was ruined cause someone decided to turn to do an inner >:(

29.9, 27.9, 28.8, 28.7 + 26.5, 28.3, 27.6, 27.8
Comfortable workout today both cardiovascular and muscle wise. Felt good to get some fast reps in before regionals
Indoor WU but my hip flexor was hurting so I just decided to do an easy run

Disappointment-fueled cooldown
Finished out my regionals training week with this run. Definitely felt the Florida vibes with this run cause it was just a fun cruise. 10/10
On EOD for now since I'm recovering between seasons. Glad that I'm getting a break
Regular scheduled run before Coronavirus decided to fuck on everyone

Here we go ladies and gents.
So, woke up at 9am to get the body ready and eat for my self-projected 12pm start time for the 5k. Was feeling pretty pumped for this with some good music and felt ready to do this time trial. 

Side notes before: I invited my high school friends (some runners, some not) to come out and watch my 5k and come cheer me on even though they can't pace. I told them a 12pm start and they all told me that they would come. My family has one car right now. As well, the track is about 4 miles from me, 10 minute drive.

Here's where it goes to shit. At 11am I start heading out for the track. I go to start the car and it doesn't start. oof #1. We call a tow and they say that the car won't be ready until tomorrow. oof #2. As it is getting to 11:30, I say fuck it and order an Uber cause I don't want to be late for the time I gave. oof #3. 

Note: I am trying to practice social distancing to the best of my ability but I was really trying to get this in and was desperate. 

Ok so, I get in the uber and get to track at 11:50. Nobody is there. oof #4. I shake it off and say they'll get here while I'm doing my warmup, no problem. Get back at 12:10, still nobody is there. oof #5. Get only one text from my friend who can't come because his dad is being cautious with his asthma. oof #6. I love this guy and I'm ok with him cause he texted me and I know he's really at risk. 

Put the work in, got the schmoney, gave the track the schmoke. 

If I knew that people weren't coming, I would have just done it in the streets by my house and not had to deal with all this shit. oof #7. Not driving there means I gotta get back so I say FUCK IT, and just do my cooldown WITH MY BAG OF ALL MY STUFF. oof #8. Then walk the rest of the way back. oof #9. But the walk wasn't bad cause I got iced coffee on the way back and listened to some good music for 4 miles. 

If you read that, damn thank you. Just need to get that out and that I'm really missing you guys. I would do anything to be back at UR

This week is Purple Moonlight Pages, a hip-pop jazz album made by RAP Ferreira. This album lived off of the sound and the different  instruments. It kept me engaged the entire time as each song the beat, instruments, and flow changed. The use of that smooth saxophone and then the inclusion of various trumpets along with the so solid drums in the back and then the delight of the piano sounds. Each song was produced so well and you can tell in the sounds of Noncipher, An Idea is a work of art, and Mythical . Where Noncipher has that sax sound, An Idea is a Work of Art with the piano and drums, and then Mythical combines all of my favorite sounds from the album. 
Lyrically, the album has some super super high points. Decorum opens the album so well, and Cycles just keeps the theme of having art in the world is what we have to use to fight. Cause we can't fight with money or power but we can fight with words and show the truth and that's the most important. And No Starving Artists continues with this theme that we need artists and art because they are so valuable. And then Master Plan finishes the album so perfectly. He sings about how the world is this beautiful place and that as long as we have music and art that the world will prosper and be happy because of that music.
However, there were also some songs that were ok and I felt like they didn't contribute much. Laundry makes sense that he is forced to do laundry to make money but there's a point where he is just saying laundry for 30 seconds. As well, Pinball was ok, again lyrically bland and didn't make sense.

Overall, this album was pretty good and the themes were so solid and meaningful and then the sounds just created such an amazing background to the beauty of the lyrics. 
Verdict: 8/10

This week was IGOR by Tyler the Creator. Imo this was a massive set up from Flower Boy and felt like his best work by miles. I wasn't disappointed by any song except New Magic Wand. Igor's theme is a very good opener and establishes this new sound of the album. The Earfquake hits you like a truck of absolute VIBES. Such a catchy sound that just establishes that this album is going to be a great hip-hop/pop album that combines the interesting and experimental sounds and catchiness of pop while also having that personality from the artist. The bangers continue with I Think and A Boy is a Gun. We get to see some lyrics now from Tyler and his love life while also being able to head bang the hell out of this. The story is being told of this one relationship as he is falling in love but violence eventually gets in the way, which is seen in the following songs up to a Boy is a Gun. Then we hit the backend after he does what he has to do to survive that he ruined that relationship but he is thankful for everything that the person did. And eventually wants forgiveness. The album theme is kinda spelled out. But you get it. 
The sounds also just hit different and the album overall is a banger and a half.
Verdict: 10/10

ASTROWORLD by Travis Scott is up this week. Another well renowned album and more experimentation in this psychedelic hip-hop genre which really fits Travis's style imo. However, I found myself continuing to dip in and out of listening to the music. I was really engaged and pumped up when some of his bangers were playing, and he has a TON on this album. Stargazing, Sicko Mode, Skeletons,  Wake Up, 5% Tint, NC-17, Can't Say, Yosemite. But as good as these songs were, I found the other songs to be equally bad or uninteresting. It had that style and beat that I liked but there wasn't anything special. The beat switches on Sicko Mode with Drake's features swept that song. And the instrumentals on the other songs gave such a hype feeling or a calm, smooth, psychedelic feeling. But the other songs didn't do either and didn't accomplish much.
I still have to give credit for how well this album is made and the absolute energy it gives off. Some songs are even on playlists so ASTROWORLD will never leave.

Today was another one of Kanye, The Life of Pablo. Maybe it's cause it's nostalgia of freshman year but nonetheless good album. Ultralight Beam starts the album hard with what can be compared to a Jesus is King song but like 1000x better. Then Father Stretch my Hands pt.1 is something. One hand it's great to sing and rave to but the lyrics are iffy. We all know what bars I'm talking about. Then pt.2 is trash, desiigner ain't good and that holds true for this song. After famous, we get into this weird section, where it's just soft reflection but also like cursing his family and shit. Then waves is some steak sauce, good instrumentals and good enough lyrics. Then we have some more reflective songs which are good examples of solid experimentation from Kanye. After the sounds of Wolves, we get my favorite section of album starting at No More Parties in LA up to Saint Pablo. No More Parties in LA is criminally underrated and needs some more love. Overall, the album is kinda all over the place but it makes sense as well, you can absolutely vibe to it.

Scott's album review is back after me being bad about it. To make up, I got two today. Ventura by Anderson .Paak and Shoot for the Stars Aim for the Moon by Pop Smoke. 
So Ventura, after having recently finding Paak, took this 30 min album for a ride and I enjoyed this listen very much. It was a superb R&B influenced hip hop album that had some amazing instrumentals on the keyboard and drums. And the vocals were also a soothing but engaging voice. Some really good songs but then some were also lackluster at points but very solid.
Verdict: 7.5/10
Now, Pop Smoke. A complete 180 to some of the best trap music I have heard in a while. As Pop Smoke died soon after MTW2, this posthumous album is very posthumous as the features are everywhere. To the point where Pop Smoke is barely rapping in some songs. But when he does, lord it is some fire. His bars go off and he delivers them all flawlessly. Aim for the moon, Gangstas, Snitching, The Woo were the highlight songs as this album has a good mix of new trap sounds and the traditional ones. I would have loved to listen to the growth of this sound.
Verdict: 9/10

4:47, 4:55, 5:05, 4:47 (pace)
I will like to formally apologize for taking us out in a sub-70 but my race tactic was go hard or go home, be aggressive and taking a commanding lead. Had that for the first mile and I was feeling really confident as we were clicking 72's. Then Sam passed me and gave me an extra competitive drive but then come lap 7 I wanted to get back in front and lead but every straightaway I couldn't pass and would tuck behind for the turn. This happened for 3 laps and honestly destroyed my mentality. I think I had the lead for lap 8+9, I run 10 seconds faster. That would have been a great confidence booster but alas, it is a mistake that I'm able to learn from.
Also, preparation was really really wonky today and I think that contributed. Slept less than 5 hours cause I was an anxious mess. Went to bed really ready and fresh then woke up and had some heavy ass legs. The strides just felt, heavy and way too much work. As well, breakfast plan was bad too cause Doug didn't open until 8 and didn't eat a lot. But my stomach felt so full leading up to the race, and just felt like throwing up leading up to the race. 
But enough complaining, another PR and another good day of competitive racing. Felt really happy that I was able to push Sam to a really good PR, and happy how long I lasted

Onto to finals at number 12. Went just like previous years. Slower opening then fast closing. Some tactical moments to improve but also some things I did well. Got choppy after the 100m cause I got boxed in with the one guy going too slow then the field closing in on the right. This forced a lane 2 move after the 250 and then made sure to get on second's shoulder just like I wanted to. After the 600, I went side to side with second which was needed for being in heat 1 cause heat 2 had the ability to adapt to our times. Then at ~850, went ahead and then had a good decision not to chase the guy way in front cause I would bridged the gap and put more energy than needed for myself to be in a good position. Rolling at 1100, picked it up and held off the pack until 1450 where three went ahead but I was still able to qualify as the next guy didn't hit ahead. 58.8 closing which isn't awful but could be better, but then again it's what needed. Keep being respectfully cocky
